snippet.textDisplay:
It is unfortunate they both couldn't communicate better and be honest. It also takes a while to open up to someone about these things.

In my personal opinion sexual health is important and both consenting adults should have had a more mature discussion. For example, take time, get to know each other and then ask "as we are getting to know each other, this is my past, is there anything I should know about you?". Trust takes a while to build, that's why I feel (again my personal opinion, I respect if people have a disagreement), these quick matches may not always work.
